  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Shelter interventions to Enhance IDPs and Returnees&apos; Resilience in Aleppo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Based on rapid assessment of humanitarian needs among the displaced/evacuated persons from East Aleppo, which was carried out by UNHCR and its partners in the field, provision of shelter activities is proposed as an emergency and post emergency response to the humanitarian needs in order to save and sustain lives. The proposed activities are multi-sectoral response, involving coordination with WASH and Early Recovery Sectors. 

Shelter is a critical need and a major concern of the displaced population, due to the recent events in Aleppo, in order to ensure a dignified way of living. The displaced people from eastern Aleppo either headed to urban areas to be hosted by relatives and friends, living in damaged houses, accommodated in partially rehabilitated hangars that were made available by the Governorate of Aleppo, or have returned to their original areas.  

The following shelter activities are proposed to be implemented under this project: 
1.	Provision of emergency shelter through:
	Shelter kits interventions.
	Light shelter support for damaged houses.
2.	Provision of long-term/permanent shelter interventions targeting returnees who returned to their original houses in East Aleppo.</narrative>
  </description>
